    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is essentially a neutral third-party vault where funds and documents are held securely until the closing conditions are met, ensuring neither the buyer nor the seller can move forward prematurely. In Toronto, this is crucial because it protects both parties from fraud or last-minute changes, keeping the transaction on track until the final deed transfer. Without it, you'd be risking your hard-earned cash or your new home before everything is officially settled.\n\nThink of it like a secure box that only opens when the contract says it should, with the escrow agent acting as the gatekeeper. If you're worried about the process, just remember that the escrow officer is there to make sure every step is followed exactly as written. It's a standard safety measure that keeps the whole deal legitimate and fair.",
